column262:
5. SPOTLIGHT ISSUES
 
5.1 - CONDITIONS
5.2 - CONSUMPTION
5.3 - COMPOSITION
5.4 - CLIMATE

Reports published after Jan 18, where relevant to indicator
column264: 5.1 - CONDITIONS: According to the ILO, working conditions are at the core of decent and dignified work. Generally speaking, working conditions cover a broad range of topics and issues, from working time (hours of work, rest periods, and work schedules) to remuneration, as well as the physical conditions and mental demands that exist in the workplaces. Here, we put the spotlight on some of the more egregious, thorny, endemic or hidden working conditions issues.
